\f0\fs24 \cf0 An unleveling of the shoulders is generally a sign that there is an underlying scoliosis in the spine.  This should be evaluated by a physician to determine its severity and whether it is progressive.  Stretches and strengthening exercises should be done on a regular basis to stretch the tight (usually low) side and strengthen the weak (usually high) side.}